City Power is pulling the plug on some houses at an upmarket Dainfern estate, in northern Johannesburg. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Residents of a posh Johannesburg suburb got a shock on Wednesday morning. Parts of areas in Dainfern had their electricity switched off, because of illegal connections, bridged meters and tampered meters. READ: Power cuts here to stay - Expert At least 204 properties owe the city R13-million in revenue. City Power says some households haven't paid, while others have illegal power connections. 